#. Tag: title
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preface"
msgstr "Predgovor"

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Many professionals are increasingly embracing Debian GNU/Linux, whose goal to create a rich and flexible distribution that does not require too much maintenance fits their expectations. They generally appreciate its robustness and reliability, its automation of secondary tasks, as well as the coherence brought by the strict application of specifications and therefore the durability of achievements and skills."
msgstr ""
"Veliki broj profesionalaca sve više koristi Debian GNU/Linux, koji kao cilj "
"želi stvoriti bogatu i fleksibilnu distribuciju koja ne zahtijeva previše "
"održavanja, no ipak ispunjava sve zahtjeve. Generalno se cijeni robusnost i "
"pouzdanost sistema, njegova automatizacija sekundarnih zadataka, te "
"dosljednost sistema koja je omogućena primjenom točno određenih "
"specifikacija, koje na taj način omogućuje profesionalcima da postignu "
"trajnost znanja i vještina."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "At the same time, many influential actors in the computing industry have now come to understand the strategic interest of using an elaborate distribution that is not managed by a commercial entity. Some of their customers also understand — following the same logic — that a software platform that does not depend on agreements between suppliers reduces the constraints they will have after the purchase."
msgstr ""
"U isto vrijeme, mnogo utjecajnih faktora u računalnoj industriji je počelo "
"shvaćati strateški interes u korištenju elaborirane distribucije koja nije "
"pod kontrolom komercijalnog tijela. Neki od njihovih klijenata također "
"shvaćaju, prateći istu logiku, da programska platforma koja ne ovisi o "
"dogovorima između dobavljača smanjuje zapreke na koje bi naišli nakon "
"kupovine."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finally, many beginners discover Debian through the Knoppix and Ubuntu projects, while others “look under the hood” because they want to avoid empiricism."
msgstr ""
"U konačnici, veliki broj početnika otkrije Debian kroz Knoppix i Ubuntu "
"projekte, dok drugi  jer žele izbjeći empiricizam."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "Debian — which used to be low-profile — was first adopted by passionate users, who were often attracted by the spirit it embodies. They found a project with clear goals and visible achievements, whose developers focus on creating a good design <emphasis>before</emphasis> building — thereby rejecting the deadlines that often compromise the quality of so many other software projects. Debian is led by its very actors. In other words, Debian users join a project that fully benefits from the advantages of free software… so as to produce free software themselves."
msgstr ""
"Debian - koji je bio niskog profila - je prvotno bio prihvaćen od strane "
"strastvenih korisnika, koji su često bili privučeni karmom koja okružuje "
"Debian. Pronašli su projekt sa jasnim ciljevima i vidljivim postignućima, "
"čiji se developeri fokusiraju na stvaranje kvalitetnog dizajna "
"<emphasis>prije</emphasis> unaprijed - na taj način odbacujući vremenske "
"rokove koji često kompromitiraju kvalitetu i ostalih projekata. Debian je "
"vođen od strane samih korisnika. Drugim riječima, korisnici Debian sustava "
"se priključuju projektu koji je u prednosti jer koristi besplatan "
"software... na način da upravo korisnici stvaraju besplatan software."

#. Tag: para
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <citetitle>Debian Administrator's Handbook</citetitle> will guide you on your way to autonomy. It could only be written by authors who master both the technical aspects and the inner workings of the Debian project, and who know the needs of seasoned professionals as well as enthusiasts. Raphaël Hertzog and Roland Mas had the required qualities and managed to create and update this book. I thank them very much for their work and have no doubt that reading this book will be both helpful and pleasant."
msgstr ""
"<citetitle>Debian Administrator's Handbook</citetitle> će vas voditi na putu "
"prema samostalnosti. Knjiga je mogla biti napisana samo od strane autora "
"koji vladaju tehničkim aspektima Debian-a te samim sustavom iznutra, te koji "
"znaju prepoznati potrebe profesinalaca isto kao i one entuzijasta. Raphaël "
"Hertzog i Roland Mas posjeduju kvalitete koje su potrebne za stvaranje ove "
"knjige. Puno im hvala na njihovom trudu i nemam sumnje da će čitanje ove "
"knjige biti korisno i ugodno."

